{
  "local_port": 35408,
  "remote_port": 443,
  "prompt": "What are some useful websites for students?",
  "response": "Here are some useful websites for students across various fields:\n\n1. **Khan Academy** - Provides free online courses, lessons, and practice in various subjects including math, science, and humanities. (khanacademy.org)\n\n2. **Coursera** - Offers online courses, specializations, and degrees from universities around the world. (coursera.org)\n\n3. **edX** - Another platform for online courses from top institutions, with a focus on higher education. (edx.org)\n\n4. **Duolingo** - A popular platform for learning new languages interactively. (duolingo.com)\n\n5. **Quizlet** - A tool for creating and studying flashcards and interactive games for various subjects. (quizlet.com)\n\n6. **Wolfram Alpha** - A powerful computational engine useful for solving equations, performing calculations, and getting detailed information. (wolframalpha.com)\n\n7. **Grammarly** - A writing assistant that helps with grammar, punctuation, and style suggestions. (grammarly.com)\n\n8. **Google Scholar** - A free search engine for scholarly literature, providing access to many articles and publications. (scholar.google.com)\n\n9. **TED-Ed** - Educational videos and lessons created by educators and animators across the world. (ed.ted.com)\n\n10. **Project Gutenberg** - Offers over 60,000 free eBooks, including many classic literatures. (gutenberg.org)\n\n11. **MIT OpenCourseWare** - Free lecture notes, exams, and videos from MIT's courses. (ocw.mit.edu)\n\n12. **National Geographic Kids** - A resource for students interested in science and exploration. (kids.nationalgeographic.com)\n\n13. **SparkNotes** - Provides study guides for literature, poetry, history, film, and philosophy. (sparknotes.com)\n\n14. **Chegg** - Offers textbook rentals, homework help, and online tutoring. Some services require a subscription. (chegg.com)\n\n15. **Slader** (now part of Quizlet) - Provides solutions to textbook exercises and user-generated questions. (quizlet.com/explanations)\n\nThese resources can be immensely helpful for students in managing their coursework, supplementing their learning, and exploring new interests.",
